35.10	Ulema	Ulama	Ulama (Arabic: â€Ž , singular , "scholar"), also spelt ulema, refers to the educated class of Muslim legal scholars engaged in the several fields of Islamic studies. They are best known as the arbiters of sharia law. While the ulama are well versed in legal fiqh (jurisprudence) being Islamic lawyers, some of them also go on to specialize in other fields, such as hadith or tafseer.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/69/Constantinople%281878%29-ulema.png/180px-Constantinople%281878%29-ulema.png
